{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"coaching":[{"coaching":"Pin down restorative operator steps after accidental compaction with a concrete worked example.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f5fed8d2a4cd03ac0","fa892e914ebc32dbd"],"move_id":"6","move_name":"specification by example","subject":"restorative operator steps after accidental compaction"},{"coaching":"Propagate the revision for MCP identity creation-channel coverage gap to the child tickets.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f465c5470ad8b1ecc"],"move_id":"11","move_name":"propagate to children","subject":"MCP identity creation-channel coverage gap"},{"coaching":"Plan how actual downgrade path verification approach will be verified in-session — restate any deferred or unobservable success target as an observable proxy.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f8024563847e5545a"],"move_id":"9","move_name":"plan the verification","subject":"actual downgrade path verification approach"},{"coaching":"Test the riskiest assumption behind immutability enforcement for creation_channel field first.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f7a14f7ffb125980a"],"move_id":"4","move_name":"riskiest-assumption test","subject":"immutability enforcement for creation_channel field"},{"coaching":"Pin down CREATE-time enum validation across all channel values with a concrete worked example.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f870cf049b247bf83"],"move_id":"6","move_name":"specification by example","subject":"CREATE-time enum validation across all channel values"},{"coaching":"Plan how runtime show/list/search projection verification will be verified in-session — restate any deferred or unobservable success target as an observable proxy.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f64d0ae10d020e0c3"],"move_id":"9","move_name":"plan the verification","subject":"runtime show/list/search projection verification"},{"coaching":"Pin down import-channel injection mechanism in NDJSON path with a concrete worked example.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f6f58de62e34e53bd"],"move_id":"6","move_name":"specification by example","subject":"import-channel injection mechanism in NDJSON path"},{"coaching":"Record an ADR for architectural decision record for this novel audit pattern — it reads like a one-way door.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f638e213ca1bdd6b2"],"move_id":"8","move_name":"ADR / one-way-door","subject":"architectural decision record for this novel audit pattern"},{"coaching":"Run a quick pre-mortem on all-at-once production rollout without feature flag: how could this plan fail?","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["fa6cd8a4702458c3a"],"move_id":"3","move_name":"pre-mortem","subject":"all-at-once production rollout without feature flag"},{"coaching":"Weigh at least one structural alternative for legacy inference scope boundary between child stories.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f29fd68ae607c41de"],"move_id":"5","move_name":"weigh alternatives","subject":"legacy inference scope boundary between child stories"}],"coverage":{"counts":{"advisory_overflow":0,"advisory_surfaced":11,"blocking":0,"dropped":6,"indeterminate":0},"det":{"P1":{"ac_items":12,"blocking":false,"clarity_score":7,"name":"readiness-shape","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P2":{"blocking":false,"name":"resolution","ran":true,"references":0,"resolved":0,"status":"pass"},"P3":{"blocking":false,"name":"package-existence","packages":0,"ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P4":{"ac_items":12,"blocking":false,"desc_chars":12045,"file_impact":8,"name":"oversize","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P5":{"blocking":false,"children":3,"edges":3,"name":"task-dag","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P6":{"ac_items":12,"blocking":false,"name":"ac-quality","ran":true,"status":"pass","verify_commands_linted":4,"verify_lint_abstained":4},"P7":{"blocking":false,"destructive_hits":[],"name":"destructive-sniff","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P8":{"blocking":false,"budget_tokens":868000,"name":"reviewability","plan_tokens":3028,"ran":true,"status":"pass","worst_parent_child_pair_tokens":5047},"P9":{"applicable":false,"blocking":false,"file_impact":8,"name":"file-impact-coverage","ran":true,"status":"pass"}},"llm_ran":true,"metrics":{"claim_path":"no-llm/no-network (structural; the fast claim check is a local HMAC verify)","det_ms":260.1,"llm_calls":23,"llm_ms":701006.7,"total_ms":701385.9,"verify_requests":43},"remediation":{"baseline":"signature","eligible":false,"reasons":{"code_unchanged":false,"plan_changed":true,"prior_sidecar":true,"registry_unchanged":true,"signed":true,"within_window":true}},"routing":{"agent_tier":["G3","G4","G6","T1","T10","T11","T13","T14","T3","T5c","T8"],"single_turn":["COH","E1","E2","E3","F1","F4","G5","T12","T2","T4","T5e","T7"]}},"findings":[{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add a restorative fallback to the downgrade procedure: specify a pre-downgrade checkpoint step (e.g., verify no SNAPSHOT exists for affected tickets, or snapshot the raw event log) so that if compaction runs on the old binary, affected tickets can be identified and recovery is possible (e.g., re-run reducer on retained raw events after re-upgrading).","cohort":["T4","T7"],"criteria":["T4"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'The only binary rollback is a full downgrade to the immediately pre-feature binary, which hides the field and has an explicit first-compaction DATA LOSS RISK.'","'Before deploying the old binary, operators must stop every scheduled or manual rebar compact invocation and keep compaction/event retirement stopped for the entire downgrade window'","No event-log backup, compaction-dryrun gate, or restore-from-raw-events procedure is specified for the case where the compaction pause is violated.","T4 checklist: 'The remedy is an explicit rollback/back-out plan or expand-contract — acknowledgement alone is insufficient.'"],"finding":"The rollback plan is purely preventive — it tells operators to stop `rebar compact` before downgrading — but provides no restorative path if an operator runs compaction on the old binary anyway. The T4 criterion requires an explicit rollback/back-out plan, not just a preventive warning; once the bad compaction occurs, creation_channel is silently and permanently lost from affected tickets with no described recovery.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f5fed8d2a4cd03ac0","impact":0.67,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions — 'Compaction preserves creation_channel' paragraph and Risks and Mitigations — 'Snapshot data loss' bullet; AC item for docs/concurrency.md","norm_id":"n6869a18261acc559","priority":0.67,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["Operator overlooks the guidance and runs `rebar compact` on the old binary; all newly compacted tickets permanently lose creation_channel with no recovery.","Automated compaction job (cron/CI) is not paused; partial compaction occurs silently before the operator notices."],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"Extend the downgrade section to require: (1) before switching binaries, record the set of ticket IDs that have been compacted (SNAPSHOT present) under the new binary so they are known to carry creation_channel; (2) if old-binary compaction is detected post-hoc (e.g., via a SNAPSHOT missing creation_channel), define recovery as: upgrade to new binary, run `rebar rebuild-snapshot` (or equivalent) on the affected ticket IDs to regenerate creation_channel from the raw CREATE event. Add this to docs/concurrency.md and gate it with a test.","tier":"LLM","validity":1.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"medium","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"medium","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Confirm that MCP create_identity creation reports creation_channel=mcp, and add a test case for it in 6fe2's AC2 proof (or explicitly assign it).","cohort":["G3","G4"],"criteria":["G3","G4"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Parent AC1: 'CLI, MCP, plus direct Python creation report cli, mcp, plus python respectively across standard tickets, ideas, identities, plus session logs.'","6fe2 AC2: 'MCP create_ticket, create_idea, and first-use log_session persist and return creation_channel=mcp.' — MCP create_identity is absent.","_mcp_writes.py line 83-84: create_identity calls rebar.create_identity(..., return_alias=True) which calls _identity.create_identity_core through _lib_writes.py.","6fe2 What section: 'Add creation_channel=python keyword parameters to create_identity_core and ensure_identity_for. Local library callers use that default' — but the MCP path through rebar.create_identity also becomes a 'local library caller' and would default to python, not mcp.","6fe2 Files: lists _mcp_writes.py but the AC does not name create_identity as an MCP case to prove.","container pairing: parent + 568c-b44b-7e2b-4d87/6fe2-ab22-c231-4a41/e622-a596-3ceb-4f74"],"finding":"Child 6fe2's AC2 covers only 'MCP create_ticket, create_idea, and first-use log_session' for the mcp channel, but the parent AC1 requires 'identities' to also report the invoking interface (mcp) for MCP creation. The MCP create_identity tool in _mcp_writes.py calls rebar.create_identity → _identity.create_identity_core, but the threading mechanism from the MCP boundary through the library facade to create_identity_core is not specified in 6fe2, and the AC does not name MCP identity creation as a covered case.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f465c5470ad8b1ecc","impact":0.85,"is_primary":null,"location":"child 6fe2-ab22-c231-4a41 — Acceptance Criteria AC2 and Scope/Files sections","norm_id":"nd5a97cd5f5ec003a","priority":0.6611,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["An auditor inspects an identity ticket created via MCP and finds creation_channel=python instead of mcp, making MCP creation indistinguishable from direct Python library calls.","The test -k mcp in 6fe2's AC2 may not include create_identity, leaving the MCP identity creation channel unvalidated and silently reporting the wrong value."],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"In 6fe2, either (a) add a creation_channel parameter to rebar.create_identity in _lib_writes.py and thread mcp from _mcp_writes.py, or (b) add a test case for MCP create_identity to the -k mcp test and confirm the threading mechanism in the What/Files sections. Add 'MCP create_identity' explicitly to 6fe2 AC2.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.7778,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"yes","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"low","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add at least one AC (or a documented manual validation step with a script) that exercises the rollback three-state matrix — e.g., a test that serializes a new-code SNAPSHOT and verifies an old-binary-equivalent reader (simulated via schema stripping logic) handles it as specified for each of the three cases.","cohort":["E3","T12"],"criteria":["T12"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["The plan describes three states: (a) old binary + new SNAPSHOT retains creation_channel; (b) old binary first compaction of raw CREATE events loses the field; (c) never-compacted ticket retains the value in CREATE but old reader hides it.","AC7 and AC8 test compaction and SNAPSHOT-only replay with the NEW binary — neither AC exercises the old-binary behavior.","No AC invokes the pre-feature binary against post-feature data to verify the three-state matrix holds.","The AC for docs/concurrency.md (AC12) proves the documentation exists but not that the behavior is correct."],"finding":"The rollback three-state schema matrix is documented in prose but no AC tests the actual downgrade path — specifically that an old binary reading new-code SNAPSHOTs, new CREATE events, or never-compacted tickets behaves as specified.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f8024563847e5545a","impact":1.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions — rollback matrix; Acceptance Criteria — compaction ACs","norm_id":"n571174785daa1b95","priority":0.625,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["If operators initiate a rollback and the old binary behaves differently from what the three-state matrix predicts (e.g., process_snapshot does NOT restore unknown compiled_state keys as claimed), auditors will get silently wrong data without any test catching this discrepancy.","The claim that 'the old strip policy removes only updated_at plus signature' is a code assumption that could be invalidated by an unrelated patch; without a cross-binary behavioral test, this assumption is unverified."],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"missing_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add an AC (or explicit Architecture Decision) specifying that the reducer ignores/rejects `creation_channel` on any non-CREATE event type, and prove it with a test that sends a mutation event containing `creation_channel` and asserts the compiled_state value is unchanged.","cohort":["E3","T12"],"criteria":["E3"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Title states 'immutable ticket creation channel'.","'Jira outbound bind/sync events preserve the already-reduced creation_channel and never supply a replacement value' — this is a behavioral statement about one call site, not a reducer-level invariant.","No AC tests that a UPDATE/PATCH/BIND event containing a creation_channel field is rejected or ignored by the reducer.","No AC tests that a second CREATE event for the same ticket cannot change creation_channel."],"finding":"The plan claims `creation_channel` is 'immutable' in the title and Architecture Decisions, but provides no enforcement mechanism or test that rejects a subsequent event attempting to overwrite the field on an existing ticket.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f7a14f7ffb125980a","impact":1.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Title: 'Track immutable ticket creation channel'; Architecture Decisions — 'Add creation_channel to CREATE data and compiled ticket state'","norm_id":"n920650fe69f0d088","priority":0.625,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["A future ingress or buggy writer emits an UPDATE event with a creation_channel field; without reducer enforcement, the compiled_state could silently mutate, breaking the immutability guarantee the title promises.","A Jira outbound sync event that inadvertently includes creation_channel in its payload would overwrite the recorded value."],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"In the reducer's compiled_state projection logic, treat creation_channel as a CREATE-only field: set it once from the first CREATE event and ignore it on all subsequent events. Add a corresponding test: `pytest -q tests/unit/reducer/test_creation_channel_immutability.py -k 'mutation_cannot_overwrite'`.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"missing_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"medium","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"moderate","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Clarify in Architecture Decisions that writer-side enum validation applies to create_core callers (CLI/MCP/Python/import) but the Jira inbound path sets the channel value directly in CREATE data and relies on a reader-side fallback or a separate assertion; alternatively, add a lightweight validation call (e.g. assert channel in VALID_CHANNELS) inside _inbound_create_write_create_event to close the gap.","cohort":["G6"],"criteria":["G6"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan: 'The shared core carries and validates the declared internal value; it does not inspect the call stack.'","Codebase: _inbound_create_write_create_event builds create_data and calls _write_event_file directly (apply_inbound_records.py lines 125–145), never routing through composer.create_core.","The plan itself acknowledges the two seams: 'The current code has two creation seams. Local surfaces converge on src/rebar/_commands/composer.py:create_core … while Jira inbound creation composes CREATE data in src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/apply_inbound_records.py.'","ABSENCE: No plan text describes a validation step for the channel value on the Jira inbound path."],"finding":"The plan states 'The shared core carries and validates the declared internal value' (Architecture Decisions), implying CREATE-time enum validation applies to all channels including 'jira'. However, the Jira inbound creation path in apply_inbound_records.py calls _write_event_file directly, bypassing create_core entirely — so the channel value written to Jira-originated CREATE events never passes through the proposed validator in create_core. If a future maintainer adds a new Jira inbound writer or mistypes the literal 'jira', no writer-side guard catches it.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f870cf049b247bf83","impact":0.85,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions — 'The shared core carries and validates the declared internal value'; also src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/apply_inbound_records.py:_inbound_create_write_create_event (line 125, create_data dict)","norm_id":"n0fd761d92706a3f5","priority":0.5312,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["A future inbound Jira writer uses a typo or an off-vocabulary string; the error is silent at write time and surfaces only as an unexpected value in compiled state.","The plan's stated invariant that new writes always record a concrete non-unknown value cannot be enforced by create_core for the jira channel, only by convention."],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"Add one sentence to Architecture Decisions: 'The inbound Jira materialization path sets creation_channel directly in CREATE data and does not route through create_core; a module-level assertion or constant reference in apply_inbound_records.py pins the vocabulary for that path.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"medium","divergent_implementation":"low","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"low","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Document whether `rebuild_snapshot_from_full_log` (which reduces from `.retired` files via `include_retired=True`) can recover `creation_channel` from a SNAPSHOT produced by an old binary during a violated downgrade window, and either add a compensating-forward recovery procedure to `docs/concurrency.md` or explicitly state the data is irrecoverable to justify the unconditional compaction-pause requirement.","cohort":["T11"],"criteria":["T11"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan: 'a first old-code compaction of raw creation-bearing CREATE events would produce a SNAPSHOT without creation_channel, which is why compaction is prohibited during the window'","Plan explicitly labels this 'DATA LOSS RISK' but provides only the preventive operator precondition, not a recovery path after violation","docs/concurrency.md confirms .retired files are kept permanently: '.retired files are kept permanently for now — an accepted storage tradeoff that guarantees a folded source is never lost'","compact.py rebuild_snapshot_from_full_log already reduces from include_retired=True, meaning .retired CREATEs carrying creation_channel are still accessible after old-binary compaction","ABSENCE: the plan does not state whether fsck --repair-snapshots / rebuild_snapshot_from_full_log can recover the field from .retired CREATEs after a constraint violation"],"finding":"The plan identifies a DATA LOSS RISK if compaction runs during a binary downgrade window, but does not specify a compensating-forward recovery path for the case where that constraint is violated. Since .retired files are retained permanently (I1/docs/concurrency.md), rebuild_snapshot_from_full_log — which reduces from the full log including .retired files — could potentially recover the creation_channel value from a stranded .retired CREATE. The plan does not affirm or deny this recovery path, leaving operators without a documented procedure if the precondition is accidentally violated.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fa892e914ebc32dbd","impact":0.67,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions section — 'The only binary rollback is a full downgrade…' paragraph; also child ticket 568c-b44b-7e2b-4d87 description — 'Document the rollback schema-state matrix'; AC line: 'docs/concurrency.md defines the full-downgrade three-state schema matrix'","norm_id":"n11c8c4036a377004","priority":0.4188,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["A scheduled rebar compact-all job fires during the downgrade window before operators can stop it. The old binary compacts a CREATE carrying creation_channel into a SNAPSHOT that omits it. The plan says this is data loss, but operators have no documented recovery procedure.","A CI pipeline or a cron job triggers a single rebar compact during the downgrade window. The operators follow the rollback guide but miss stopping one automated compact invocation."],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"Add a paragraph to the rollback guidance in `docs/concurrency.md` (and/or the plan's downgrade matrix): 'If compaction ran during the downgrade window, run `rebar fsck --repair-snapshots` after re-deploying the new binary — `rebuild_snapshot_from_full_log` reduces from `.retired` files (which are retained permanently per I1) and will re-derive the `creation_channel` value that the old-binary SNAPSHOT omitted, restoring the field from the still-extant `.retired` CREATE event.' If this recovery does NOT work (e.g., because the old binary also retired the CREATE and the HLC ordering prevents correct re-reduction), document that explicitly and add a verification step to the downgrade checklist.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"medium"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Extend AC #6's proof command to include at least one test file (e.g., `tests/interfaces/facades/test_creation_channel_output.py`) that exercises `rebar show`, `rebar list`, and `rebar search` command output and asserts the six-value enum field is present and correct in their results.","cohort":["E2","F1"],"criteria":["F1"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["\"Prove with uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/contracts/test_schema_ticket_state.py tests/interfaces/contracts/test_schema_outputs.py tests/interfaces/io/test_export_ndjson.py && python -m rebar.schemas.gen_types --check\"","No test file targeting `show`, `list`, or `search` runtime output is cited; the tests named are schema/contract/export tests only.","The Success Criteria section separately states 'Auditors can distinguish cli, mcp, python, jira, and import creation through existing show/list/search state projections', reinforcing that runtime projection coverage is intended."],"finding":"AC #6 claims show/list/search projections expose the six-value enum, but the cited proof command covers only schema-contract tests and type-generation checks — no test exercises the actual runtime show, list, or search command output to confirm the field appears there.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f64d0ae10d020e0c3","impact":0.55,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria — AC #6: 'TicketState schemas, generated types, show/list/search projections, plus exported NDJSON expose the six-value enum…'","norm_id":"n863e527529ef16af","priority":0.3438,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["A schema correctly defines the enum but the reducer projection omits the field from the show/list payload; the AC would pass on the schema test while the runtime behavior silently fails.","The type-generation check passes but the show command's output serializer strips unknown keys before rendering."],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"Add a `-k show or list or search` target inside `tests/interfaces/facades/test_creation_channel.py` or a dedicated contract test, then append it to AC #6's proof command alongside the existing schema tests.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Explicitly specify in e622 how creation_channel='import' is threaded into create_ticket (via _provenance.create_kwargs, a new create_ticket parameter defined in 6fe2, or a call-site kwarg), and confirm 6fe2 exposes the parameter if needed.","cohort":["G3","G4"],"criteria":["G3","G4"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Parent plan: 'Import creates a new local ticket through the import channel. Existing source_id, source_created_at, source_author, and source_env continue to describe the source record; an exported source creation_channel is not reused as the new local channel.'","import_ndjson.py line 229: 'local = create_ticket(repo_root=rr, **_provenance.create_kwargs(rec))'","_provenance.create_kwargs returns {ticket_type, title, description, priority, assignee, tags, source} — no creation_channel key.","e622 What section: 'Have src/rebar/_io/import_ndjson.py invoke the shared library creation path with the internal import channel' — but does not state whether this is done by (a) adding creation_channel to create_kwargs, (b) adding creation_channel to create_ticket's public signature in 6fe2, or (c) calling a lower-level function.","6fe2 Scope OUT: 'NDJSON import' — so 6fe2 does not add creation_channel to create_ticket's public API for import use.","container pairing: parent + 568c-b44b-7e2b-4d87/6fe2-ab22-c231-4a41/e622-a596-3ceb-4f74"],"finding":"The mechanism for injecting creation_channel='import' into the NDJSON import path is unspecified in child e622. The current import_ndjson.py calls create_ticket(**_provenance.create_kwargs(rec)), and _provenance.create_kwargs returns a fixed dict without creation_channel. The parent plan says 'An exported source creation_channel is not reused' — so _provenance.create_kwargs must NOT pass the source record's creation_channel through. But how the 'import' value reaches create_ticket (via a new parameter in create_kwargs, a new parameter in rebar.create_ticket, or a direct kwarg at the call site) is left ambiguous, creating a scope gap between e622's import attribution and 6fe2's public create_ticket signature.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f6f58de62e34e53bd","impact":0.536,"is_primary":null,"location":"child e622-a596-3ceb-4f74 — What section (import path) and child 6fe2-ab22-c231-4a41 — Scope (OUT: NDJSON import)","norm_id":"n4919c2b8397d4d0d","priority":0.335,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["If e622 adds creation_channel to _provenance.create_kwargs, it would unconditionally emit 'import' for every record, which is correct — but would then require that the source record's creation_channel is not extracted into the kwarg dict, which must be verified.","If e622 adds creation_channel to the rebar.create_ticket public signature, it crosses into 6fe2's owned signature, risking a merge conflict or interface inconsistency.","If the injection is done via a call-site kwarg (create_ticket(..., creation_channel='import')), then rebar.create_ticket must accept that parameter — an interface change that 6fe2 owns."],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"In 6fe2, add creation_channel as an optional keyword parameter to composer.create_core and rebar.create_ticket (defaulting to 'python' for library calls). In e622, add creation_channel='import' to _provenance.create_kwargs (or pass it at the call site in import_ndjson.py). Document explicitly that create_kwargs must NOT copy the source record's creation_channel field.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"medium"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add an ADR or CLAUDE.md section capturing the key architectural decisions: immutable creation-channel field, closed vocabulary rationale, Jira-only historical inference predicate (three-signal design and false-positive controls), additive-only contract, and the compaction-pause downgrade protocol — so this rationale survives ticket archival.","cohort":["T2","T5e"],"criteria":["T5e"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan mandates docs/event-schema.md, docs/output-schemas.md, docs/concurrency.md updates via AC lines — these are schema reference and operational guides, not architectural decision records.","The Architecture Decisions section contains rich rationale (inference predicate design, downgrade matrix, additive contract, compaction constraints) but it lives only in the ticket, not in a discoverable ADR or CLAUDE.md.","No AC line references an ADR file or CLAUDE.md entry.","'A novel architectural decision is captured in an ADR / CLAUDE.md / design doc update' — criterion T5e(c)."],"finding":"The plan introduces a novel architectural pattern (immutable creation-channel audit dimension with historical Jira inference and a compaction-pause downgrade protocol) but captures the architectural rationale only inside the ticket body, not in a durable ADR or CLAUDE.md update that future maintainers can discover independently of the ticket tracker.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f638e213ca1bdd6b2","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions section; Scope/Risks; AC lines for docs/event-schema.md and docs/concurrency.md","norm_id":"ndcc017538e115825","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["A future engineer adding a new ingress channel (e.g., GitHub reconciler) cannot easily find the rationale for the closed vocabulary or the inference predicate constraints without searching ticket history.","A maintainer evaluating whether to add a writer-only binary mode needs the documented rationale for why it was excluded from the MVP to avoid re-litigating the decision."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Create docs/adr/creation-channel-provenance.md (or add a ## Creation Channel Provenance section to CLAUDE.md) summarising: (1) why creation_channel is immutable and additive, (2) the closed six-value vocabulary and its extension policy, (3) the three-signal Jira inference predicate and why only jira is inferred, (4) the downgrade compaction-pause requirement and the three-state compiled_state matrix. Reference this file from the existing docs/event-schema.md. Add a corresponding AC line: 'docs/adr/creation-channel-provenance.md exists and is linked from docs/event-schema.md. Prove with ls docs/adr/creation-channel-provenance.md && grep -q creation-channel-provenance docs/event-schema.md.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.5714,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"medium","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add a lightweight deploy-time mechanism (e.g., an env-var flag `REBAR_CREATION_CHANNEL_ENABLED=1`) that gates new CREATE field writes so operators can enable the feature for a canary population before full rollout, or document why the additive-only nature of the change makes a 100%-flip safe enough to explicitly accept as a risk.","cohort":["E3","T12"],"criteria":["T12"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'The MVP deliberately has no writer-only configuration switch or intermediate binary mode; attribution defects are recovered by pausing the affected creation ingress at the deployment boundary and rolling forward.'","No AC tests a partial-rollout or flag-gated scenario.","The plan's own Risks and Mitigations section acknowledges rollback is a 'full downgrade to the immediately pre-feature binary' — an expensive, all-or-nothing operation."],"finding":"The plan explicitly rejects a feature flag or staged rollout ('The MVP deliberately has no writer-only configuration switch or intermediate binary mode'), meaning the behavior change reaches production as a 100%-traffic flip with no canary path.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fa6cd8a4702458c3a","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions — 'The public change is additive. The MVP deliberately has no writer-only configuration switch or intermediate binary mode'","norm_id":"na2c22fa6e91fd640","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["If a CREATE-path regression is discovered in production after deploy, operators have no flag to disable channel recording on new writes — they must either roll forward with a fix or execute a full binary downgrade with compaction pause.","In environments where rebar runs as a shared service across multiple teams, a 100%-traffic flip means all users are affected simultaneously with no gradual exposure."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Because the change is purely additive on CREATE writes (old readers ignore the field), the risk of a 100%-flip is lower than for a destructive change. If the team accepts this, add an explicit 'Risk Accepted' statement in Risks and Mitigations explaining why the additive contract makes staged rollout unnecessary, so reviewers can distinguish deliberate choice from oversight.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.5,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"module","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"moderate","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add a near-miss negative case to 568c's AC3 test (test_reducer_snapshot.py) that covers a pre-feature SNAPSHOT with env_id != 'reconciler' (env-override case) projecting unknown, mirroring e622's full-log negative controls.","cohort":["G3","G4"],"criteria":["G4"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["e622 Scope OUT: 'SNAPSHOT-only legacy inference, compaction'","568c What: 'After process_snapshot restores compiled_state, call _project_legacy_creation_channel(state), the state-shaped helper supplied by e622. The helper reads restored ticket_id/author/env_id, is a no-op when creation_channel is present, infers jira only for the exact legacy predicate, and otherwise writes unknown without the marker.'","Parent plan: 'Missing/None signals or legacy events written under REBAR_AUTHOR/REBAR_ENV_ID overrides intentionally project unknown.'","568c AC3: 'A pre-feature SNAPSHOT lacking both keys projects inferred Jira only for the exact three-signal predicate and otherwise unknown, while a SNAPSHOT carrying any recorded channel bypasses inference.' — the near-miss negative cases for overridden env_id in SNAPSHOT context are not listed separately for 568c.","e622 AC6: covers 'Removing or changing each inference signal independently produces creation_channel=unknown' — but this is for full-log, not SNAPSHOT-only replay.","container pairing: parent + 568c-b44b-7e2b-4d87/6fe2-ab22-c231-4a41/e622-a596-3ceb-4f74"],"finding":"Child 568c's scope and What section describe post-SNAPSHOT legacy inference by calling _project_legacy_creation_channel after process_snapshot restores compiled_state. But child e622 explicitly scopes OUT 'SNAPSHOT-only legacy inference' — meaning e622 does not deliver the SNAPSHOT path for legacy inference, only the full-log path. Child 568c owns it. However, 568c's AC3 proof ('pre-feature SNAPSHOT lacking both keys projects inferred Jira only for the exact three-signal predicate') depends on _project_legacy_creation_channel reading state['ticket_id'], state.get('author'), and state.get('env_id') from the restored compiled_state. But for a pre-feature SNAPSHOT, the compiled_state was written before the field existed, and author/env_id in compiled_state come from the CREATE event's author/env_id as projected by process_create. The parent plan and architecture decision note that inference reads 'state[ticket_id]/state.get(author)/state.get(env_id)' — but for legacy Jira records, these values in compiled_state are 'reconciler'/'reconciler' (the LEGACY_JIRA_AUTHOR/ENV_ID). This is coherent. However, the design decision that 'Missing/None signals or legacy events written under REBAR_AUTHOR/REBAR_ENV_ID overrides intentionally project unknown' creates a residual reference gap: 568c's implementation depends on e622's helper behaving correctly under SNAPSHOT restore where env_id may be 'reconciler' from old events OR an overridden value if the operator used REBAR_AUTHOR/REBAR_ENV_ID overrides. The handling of env overrides in the SNAPSHOT case is only tested in e622's full-log path, not in 568c's SNAPSHOT-only path.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f29fd68ae607c41de","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"child 568c-b44b-7e2b-4d87 — AC3 and child e622-a596-3ceb-4f74 — Scope OUT","norm_id":"n5c32a307c6648d2b","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["A legacy Jira ticket is compacted into a SNAPSHOT before this feature ships, with env_id='custom-override' because the operator used REBAR_ENV_ID during the original reconciler run. After the feature ships, SNAPSHOT-only replay for that ticket should project unknown (env override ≠ LEGACY_JIRA_ENV_ID). The 568c AC3 test covers 'otherwise unknown' but may not specifically test the env-override near-miss in the SNAPSHOT context."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"In 568c, extend tests/scripts/reducer/test_reducer_snapshot.py -k creation_channel to include a near-miss SNAPSHOT fixture where env_id is overridden (not 'reconciler'), confirming the SNAPSHOT-only legacy inference path produces unknown for that case.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Name the isolated spec-load contract test file (e.g., `tests/interfaces/contracts/test_inbound_translate_imports.py`) and add it to the relevant AC's proof command so its coverage is explicit and verifiable.","cohort":["E2","F1"],"criteria":["E2"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["\"pinned by an isolated spec-load contract test\" — the plan asserts the test exists and is required but gives no file path, module, or test suite anchor.","All other tests in the plan are cited by exact file path (e.g., tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/mutate/test_creation_channel.py, tests/interfaces/contracts/test_schema_ticket_state.py)."],"finding":"The plan requires 'an isolated spec-load contract test' to pin the absolute-import pattern for LEGACY_JIRA_AUTHOR/LEGACY_JIRA_ENV_ID in inbound_translate, but neither names the test file nor states where it lives, leaving the executor to decide its location without a stated default.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f256beff86e02ea36","impact":0.33,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions — 'inbound_translate._event_meta performs the absolute package import … pinned by an isolated spec-load contract test'","norm_id":"n01e6fb06859197c4","priority":0.1237,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["An executor uncertain whether to place the test in tests/unit/, tests/interfaces/contracts/, or a new module may choose inconsistently or omit it entirely.","The absence of a named file means no AC can reference it as proof, so the spec-load constraint is asserted in prose but never verified by a cited command."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Add a line to Architecture Decisions: 'The spec-load test lives at tests/interfaces/contracts/test_inbound_translate_imports.py and is included in the AC #5 or AC #2 proof command.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add an acceptance criterion (with a prove command referencing the spec-load contract test file) that verifies the _version.py import of LEGACY_JIRA_AUTHOR/LEGACY_JIRA_ENV_ID is isolated from the sibling reconciler package context.","cohort":["COH","E1"],"criteria":["E1"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["\"This does not depend on sibling reconciler package context and is pinned by an isolated spec-load contract test.\"","No AC references a test file or command that exercises this import-isolation contract."],"finding":"The Architecture section explicitly describes an 'isolated spec-load contract test' that pins the _version.py import path independence from the sibling reconciler package context, but no acceptance criterion covers this test or its file path — leaving a described verification artifact without a covering criterion.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fd0d36a1fd22f2428","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions (paragraph on LEGACY_JIRA_AUTHOR/LEGACY_JIRA_ENV_ID constants and inbound_translate import pattern)","norm_id":"n93b74ed1e0643c11","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["An implementer writes the import but omits or misplaces the contract test; no AC fails, so the gap goes undetected in CI.","A future refactor moves the constants out of _version.py; without an AC-backed test, the breakage is invisible."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add an AC such as: 'LEGACY_JIRA_AUTHOR and LEGACY_JIRA_ENV_ID are importable from rebar.reducer._version without the sibling reconciler package installed or on sys.path. Prove with uv run pytest -q tests/unit/reducer/test_version_constants_isolation.py.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.2857,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add a documentation AC item (or extend the docs/concurrency.md AC item) to require that the downgrade operator guidance explicitly names which consumer surfaces (show, list, search, export) lose creation_channel visibility and prescribes a notification/coordination step before the downgrade is executed.","cohort":["T4","T7"],"criteria":["T7"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'Notify downstream show/list/export consumers before any full downgrade' is referenced in the plan body but does not appear in any AC doc target.","docs/concurrency.md AC item covers only the three-state schema matrix and compaction pause — not the consumer notification procedure.","No AC item names the consumer list or where the notification obligation is documented."],"finding":"The plan references notifying 'downstream show/list/export consumers' before any full downgrade but assigns this guidance to no documentation artifact and includes no AC item to verify the notification procedure or consumer list is documented anywhere.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fc151fe3087866ef5","impact":0.55,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions — 'Notify downstream show/list/export consumers before any full downgrade and document this matrix plus the unconditional compaction pause in operator guidance.'","norm_id":"n0a75dbd98b78cc7c","priority":0.2357,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["Operator follows docs/concurrency.md for the compaction pause but is unaware of the consumer-notification requirement; downstream integrations break silently after downgrade."],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.4286,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add to the Architecture Decisions section that the creation_channel enum is canonically defined in `src/rebar/schemas/common.schema.json` (following the existing ticket_status/ticket_type pattern) and $ref'd from ticket_state.schema.json, export.schema.json, and any other consumer schema.","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Parent plan Architecture section names ticket_state.schema.json only for the {\"const\": true} rule: 'ticket_state.schema.json encodes that rule formally as {\"const\": true}'","Parent plan never mentions common.schema.json as the enum's home","Child ticket 6fe2 What section: 'Add the canonical creation-channel enum to src/rebar/schemas/common.schema.json with exactly cli, mcp, python, jira, import, unknown'","Existing pattern: ticket_status, ticket_type, relation, priority are all defined in common.schema.json and $ref'd from ticket_state.schema.json — the enum must follow this pattern but the parent plan does not state it"],"finding":"The parent plan's Architecture section specifies that the creation_channel enum vocabulary lives in ticket_state.schema.json (referencing the {\"const\": true} inference-marker encoding rule there), but never names common.schema.json as the canonical home of the enum definition itself. Child ticket 6fe2 correctly identifies common.schema.json as the canonical enum location, but an implementer reading only the parent plan cannot determine the authoritative schema file for the enum — creating a risk that it is added directly to ticket_state.schema.json (duplicating rather than $ref-ing) or to a new ad-hoc definition.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f6e2b507a0b34dde9","impact":0.264,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions section, first bullet: 'Add creation_channel to CREATE data and compiled ticket state with the closed compact vocabulary cli, mcp, python, jira, import, unknown.'","norm_id":"nda6c4cf8b39caeb7","priority":0.099,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["An implementer working from the parent plan only adds the enum inline to ticket_state.schema.json instead of common.schema.json, causing the enum to be absent from export.schema.json and fetch_ticket_output.schema.json which both $ref ticket_state.schema.json without inlining its properties.","A future schema consumer generating types from common.schema.json misses the enum because it was never added there."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"In the Architecture Decisions first bullet, append: 'The enum is defined once in common.schema.json as a $defs entry (following the ticket_status / ticket_type pattern) and $ref-d from ticket_state.schema.json and any output schema that exposes TicketState.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Specify that the ticket_state.schema.json (and common.schema.json) descriptions for `creation_channel` and `creation_channel_inferred` must include: the enum values, the absent-means-unknown legacy fallback, the inference predicate summary (three-signal Jira-only), and the trust boundary note ('diagnostic metadata, not a security attestation').","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Architecture section specifies: 'infer jira only when all creation-stable signals agree: ticket_id starts with \"jira-\", author equals LEGACY_JIRA_AUTHOR, and env_id equals LEGACY_JIRA_ENV_ID'","ticket_state.schema.json currently has no creation_channel or creation_channel_inferred fields at all (confirmed by file read)","The plan instructs adding optional fields to ticket_state.schema.json but does not specify that the schema descriptions for those fields should reference or summarize the inference rule","Existing schema precedent: source_id description includes 'Present only on tickets created by rebar import' — a consumer-facing semantic note directly in the schema"],"finding":"The inference decision rule (_project_legacy_creation_channel's three-signal predicate) is specified in the Architecture section prose, but the ticket_state.schema.json schema definition for creation_channel and creation_channel_inferred — where an executor would look for field-level semantics — contains no reference to the inference rule, the predicate, or the trust boundary. The plan relies entirely on cross-section prose co-location rather than schema-adjacent specification.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fb548846f0ab32e13","impact":0.33,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions section, third bullet: inference predicate description vs. ticket_state.schema.json field definitions","norm_id":"n0e4c20985675e147","priority":0.1414,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["A downstream consumer reads the schema description for creation_channel_inferred and sees only the {\"const\": true} structural rule, with no indication of what inference criteria produced it or that it is absent on recorded values — leading to incorrect consumer logic treating absence as 'not inferred yet' rather than 'recorded or unknown'.","A future implementer modifying the inference logic does not know the schema description needs updating because the schema contains no mention of the predicate."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.4286,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Confirm that test_schema_ticket_state.py (owned by 6fe2) validates all six enum values and not just the schema declaration, OR confirm that the combined 6fe2+e622 test suites together prove the full six-value constraint before the parent is marked complete.","cohort":["G3","G4"],"criteria":["G3"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Parent AC6: 'TicketState schemas, generated types, show/list/search projections, plus exported NDJSON expose the six-value enum with a const-true optional inference marker. Prove with uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/contracts/test_schema_ticket_state.py tests/interfaces/contracts/test_schema_outputs.py tests/interfaces/io/test_export_ndjson.py && python -m rebar.schemas.gen_types --check.'","6fe2 AC5: 'ticket_state JSON Schema, generated TicketState types, show/list/search/export outputs, and docs expose the same six-value enum and true-only optional inference marker. Prove with uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/contracts/test_schema_ticket_state.py tests/interfaces/contracts/test_schema_outputs.py tests/interfaces/contracts/test_schema_coverage.py && python -m rebar.schemas.gen_types --check.'","e622 AC8: 'TicketState output regression plus documentation checks remain green. Prove with uv run pytest -q tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/mutate/test_env_aliasing.py tests/interfaces/contracts/test_schema_outputs.py tests/interfaces/contracts/test_schema_coverage.py && make lint.' — does NOT re-run test_schema_ticket_state.py.","The six-value enum is defined in 6fe2 in common.schema.json; jira and import are values that only become exercised in live records by e622, but the schema itself includes all six from 6fe2. This is partial coverage because test_schema_ticket_state.py may validate the enum declaration but not end-to-end output for jira/import values.","container pairing: parent + 568c-b44b-7e2b-4d87/6fe2-ab22-c231-4a41/e622-a596-3ceb-4f74"],"finding":"AC6 of the parent requires that 'show/list/search projections, plus exported NDJSON expose the six-value enum.' Child 6fe2's AC5 covers this for the local three values (cli/mcp/python) and the schema shape, but the proof command for AC6 runs against test files that may not yet contain jira/import records (those are added by e622). The parent's AC6 uses a single combined proof command: 'uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/contracts/test_schema_ticket_state.py tests/interfaces/contracts/test_schema_outputs.py tests/interfaces/io/test_export_ndjson.py && python -m rebar.schemas.gen_types --check.' Child e622 also runs test_schema_outputs.py and test_export_ndjson.py in its own AC8, but the 6-value enum validation in ticket_state.schema.json is owned by 6fe2. If 6fe2 only adds the schema enum but e622 adds jira/import values that are exercised only in e622's test files, there is a partial coverage gap: the schema contract test in 6fe2's deliverable validates the shape but not all six values in use, and e622's AC does not re-run test_schema_ticket_state.py. The parent AC6 proof requires ALL six values to be validated together.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f72f969d3d0249075","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"child 6fe2-ab22-c231-4a41 — AC5 and child e622-a596-3ceb-4f74 — AC8","norm_id":"n914f87ba88d23358","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["test_schema_ticket_state.py in 6fe2 validates the schema enum declaration for all six values, but end-to-end show/export output tests for jira/import values are only in e622's test files (test_creation_channel.py, test_export_ndjson.py). If the schema_outputs test in e622 validates the full output contract, the combined union covers AC6. But if test_schema_outputs.py checks only the shape and not the specific enum values in practice, the 'expose the six-value enum' criterion is partially covered."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"In 6fe2, ensure test_schema_ticket_state.py asserts all six values are present in the enum (not just the schema JSON), including jira and import which will be written by e622 but must be in the schema from 6fe2 onward.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}}],"impact_model_version":"plan-v3","material_fingerprint":"809211f483f88a33","metrics":{"claim_path":"no-llm/no-network (structural; the fast claim check is a local HMAC verify)","det_ms":260.1,"llm_calls":23,"llm_ms":701006.7,"total_ms":701385.9,"verify_requests":43},"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","regver":"b293b9a55de591cc","runner":"pydantic_ai","schema":"plan_review_result_v2","ticket_id":"jira-reb-977","ticket_type":"epic","verdict":"PASS","verified_at_sha":"8bb261c19e933b5705a14c0625e9919e0d53634a"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"REVIEW_RESULT","timestamp":1784263909801842001,"uuid":"80befcfb-11c3-4f83-8a27-031c1811c845"}